snippet: The driver of a car that plowed through crowds on the Venice Beach boardwalk must stand trial on murder charges in the death of a newlywed woman and assault with a deadly weapon involving more than a dozen injured tourists and vendors.
abstract: California Judge Antonio Barreto Jr rules that Nathan Campbell, driver of a car that plowed through crowds on the Venice Beach boardwalk, must stand trial on murder charges and assault with a deadly weapon.
lead_paragraph: The driver of a car that plowed through crowds on the Venice Beach boardwalk must stand trial on murder charges in the death of a newlywed woman and assault with a deadly weapon involving more than a dozen injured tourists and vendors.

headline.main: California: Murder Charge in Boardwalk Death
